adm.manual.getting_started.welcome_title=Welcome
adm.manual.getting_started.welcome_text=Welcome to the AdvanceDataMonitor manual!\n\nThis mod brings advanced data visualization and AI-assisted automation to GTNH. You can render live charts in-world from AE2 and TileEntity data, control AE2 crafting with natural language, and manage tasks with the planner.\n\nUse the sidebar on the left to browse chapters. Mouse wheel scrolls long pages.

adm.manual.getting_started.core_concepts_title=Four Core Systems
adm.manual.getting_started.core_concepts_text=1. Advance Data Monitor - renders live charts (line, bar, waterfall, difference) and text in the Minecraft world from TileEntity NBT data. Each face of the monitor can be configured independently.\n\n2. AE2 Integration - three dedicated linker blocks connect to your AE2 network: Crafting Linker monitors CPUs, Advanced Storage Linker shows inventory, Network Linker aggregates full-network statistics.\n\n3. AI Assistant - natural language control via OpenAI-compatible APIs. Order crafting, withdraw items, query power/storage/recipes, teleport via Draconic Evolution gems, and manage planner tasks - all through the chat window (O key).\n\n4. Planner - a persistent task manager stored in NBT on the item. Supports adding, completing, deleting, reordering, merging entries, with an on-screen HUD overlay.

adm.manual.getting_started.quick_start_title=Quick Start
adm.manual.getting_started.quick_start_text=1. Place an Advance Data Monitor block where you want the display.\n2. Place a Crafting/Advanced Storage/Network Linker next to your AE2 network via cable adjacency.\n3. Craft a Data Imprint Tool and sneak+right-click the linker block to imprint its NBT data.\n4. Sneak+right-click the Advance Data Monitor with the imprinted tool to bind the data to a monitor face.\n5. Right-click the Advance Data Monitor to open its GUI and configure chart type, colors, scale, and more.\n6. Press O to open the AI Chat. Configure your API key in the Settings (gear icon).\n7. Press P to open the Planner if you have one in your inventory.\n\nTip: The AI Assistant works even without AE2 - you can query time, weather, position, biome, and inventory space anywhere.

adm.manual.getting_started.manual_info_title=About This Manual
adm.manual.getting_started.manual_info_text=You receive this manual once per world when you first join. If you lose it, you can:\n- Get a new one from the Tools tab in Creative mode\n- Craft it (see recipe)\n\nRight-click the manual item to open it. The chapter list on the left lets you jump between topics. Use Prev/Next buttons to flip pages. Chapter titles appear at the top of each page.

adm.manual.blocks_items.overview_title=Blocks & Items Overview
adm.manual.blocks_items.overview_text=AdvanceDataMonitor adds 4 blocks and 10 items. Each block connects to a specific part of your AE2 system and feeds data to the Data Monitor display block. The following pages describe each item in detail with its function, usage tips, and key capabilities.

