adm.manual.blocks_items.data_loom_story_title=Data Loom Cells — Lore
adm.manual.blocks_items.data_loom_story_text=AE digitizes matter into network data. AdvanceDataMonitor researchers reversed this — weaving data back into matter.\n\nEvolution:\n- Data Dust Loom Cell (basic): immature tech, only weaves the simplest form — dusts (GT dust prefix).\n- Data Form Loom Cell (advanced): full mastery, reconstructs any complex item.\n- Data Flow Cell: fluid channel, weaves data into fluids (mB units, default 1000 mB/s = 1 bucket/s).\n- Data Tide Loom Cell (advanced): fluid channel upgrade — tides of data, up to 63 fluid types.\n- Data Source Loom Cell: fluid channel, weaves data into Thaumcraft essentia (aspect fluids, default 1000 mB/s).\n\nUsage: place in ME Drive or ME Chest, mark targets in Cell Workbench, generate slowly over time. Dust/Form/Flow cells cannot mark AdvanceDataMonitor items. Output settles on a configurable interval (default 5 s); effective rates are cached on the item tooltip when markers or amplifier cards change. Weave Amplifier cards multiply output (default 4×/card, Super 16×/card, max 8 cards, multiplicative). Drains AE network energy.\n\nAdvanced Storage Linker note: contents stored inside Data Loom cells are excluded from Advanced Storage Linker statistics.\n\nConfig: [dataDustLoomCell], [dataFormLoomCell], [dataFlowCell], [dataSourceLoomCell], [dataLoomCell] (sync interval, energy drain, amplifier multipliers).
adm.manual.blocks_items.super_orange_title=Super Orange
adm.manual.blocks_items.grapple_anchor_title=Grapple Anchor
adm.manual.blocks_items.grapple_hook_title=Grapple Hook
adm.manual.blocks_items.grapple_story_title=Grapple System — Design Intent
adm.manual.blocks_items.grapple_story_text=We often spend enormous effort making beautiful bases and production lines, yet daily travel still defaults to flying, sprinting, or teleporting — flying and sprinting tie up your hands, and teleporting skips the scenery entirely.\n\nGrapple anchors and the grapple hook aim for a balance between \"getting there fast\" and \"seeing the journey\": place nodes along factory corridors, scenic bridges, production tour routes, and other key paths. Attach with the hook and glide smoothly between nodes while keeping both hands free — movement itself becomes part of the experience.\n\nQuick reference:\n- Grapple Anchor: wall/ceiling/floor mount, renameable, custom nav icon color\n- Grapple Hook: HUD hint within 12 blocks, magnetic attach within 6; shows reachable nodes through walls when attached\n- Right-click to attach, right-click again to travel, Shift to detach\n- Config category [grapple] (hint range, interact distance, travel speed, etc.)
adm.manual.item.grappleAnchor=Face-mountable anchor that forms a grapple route network across your base with the Grapple Hook.\n\nPlacement: attaches to any solid face (wall, ceiling, floor) like a thin plate embedded in your build.\n\nNaming: Shift+Right-click to set display name and selected icon color for long-distance navigation.\n\nSuggested spots: production tour paths, scenic bridges, multi-floor factory shafts, main routes from base entrance to core areas.
adm.manual.item.grappleHook=Core tool for interacting with grapple anchors. Stack size: 1.\n\nNot attached: on-screen hint within 12 blocks; world-space nav icons within 6 blocks (selected target turns green and enlarges). Right-click to attach.\n\nAttached: shows all reachable nodes; right-click to glide in a straight line to the selected target. Shift to detach.\n\nShift+Right-click: open hook settings — travel speed, show node name/distance toggles.
adm.manual.blocks_items.data_imprint_usage_title=How to Use Data Imprint
adm.manual.blocks_items.data_imprint_usage_text=The Data Imprint Tool records block state as a data snapshot and binds it to Data Monitors — it observes and displays, it does not weave matter. Workflow:\n\n1. Sneak + right-click a target TileEntity (e.g. a Crafting Linker) to imprint its NBT snapshot.\n\n2. Sneak + right-click a Data Monitor with the imprinted tool to add the location as a data source.\n\n3. Open the Data Monitor GUI and configure the binding: chart type, NBT path, colors, scale, update interval, etc.\n\n4. Plain right-click (no sneak) opens a JSON NBT viewer for finding the correct NBT path.\n\n5. Sneak + right-click air clears all imprint data from the tool.\n\nHard limit: 100 data bindings per monitor face.

adm.manual.item.advDataMonitor=The core display block of the mod. Renders live data in the Minecraft world from any TileEntity's NBT data.\n\nChart types: Line (continuous tracking), Bar (discrete comparison), 3D Bar (with depth), Waterfall (cumulative flow), Difference (delta between readings).\n\nAE2 text displays: item counts with icons, fluid storage, crafting CPU status with template expressions.\n\nMulti-face: each of the 6 sides can have independent data bindings and configurations.\n\nCustomization per binding: line color, line width, grid settings, axis colors/font, title text, scale, rotation angles, position offsets, update interval (in ticks), data limit (max visible points).\n\nDefault config: cyan (00FFFF), scale 0.3, interval 20 ticks, 100 data points max.\n\nRendering range: 128 blocks around the monitor.\n\nHardness: 2.0, light level: 1 (self-illuminated).

adm.manual.item.advCraftingLink=Connects to your AE2 network's Crafting CPU to monitor crafting activity.\n\nAuto-refresh: every 20 ticks (1 second) it polls CPU data.\n\nReports: total CPUs, busy CPUs, total/used bytes, co-processor count, final output item names, and elapsed time.\n\nSupports template expressions: write custom display text with {variables} and conditional {cond?text:alt} syntax. Example: {br}Crafting Monitor{br}Busy: {busyCpus}/{totalCpus}{br}{busyCpus:CPU#1==1?"CPU#1 working":"CPU#1 idle"}\n\nGlobal variables: totalCpus, busyCpus, cpuTotalBytes, cpuUsedBytes, totalCoProcessors.\n\nPer-CPU variables: busyCpus:Name, coProcessors:Name, usedStorage:Name, finalOutputName:Name, finalOutputAmount:Name, elapsedTime:Name.\n\nTwo scope modes: single CPU or network-wide aggregation.\n\nHardness: 3.0, blast resistance: 10.0.

adm.manual.item.advStorageLink=Connects to AE2 storage network to display item and fluid inventories.\n\nShows item icons, names, counts (with K/M/T large number formatting), and I/O delta tracking.\n\nSupports filtering: only show marked items via the Advanced Storage Link Cell.\n\n36 storage cell slots for configuration in the Advanced Storage Linker GUI.\n\nDisplay options: Items/Fluids/Essentia on/off toggles, Count/Delta/Name display switches, sorting by Default/Count/Mod, columns per row (default 4), icon size, item spacing, line spacing, text color.\n\nCan show a specific storage cell by zero-based index, or all cells.\n\nFuzzy and Inverter upgrade card support via Advanced Storage Link Cell.\n\nNote: contents stored inside Data Loom cells (Dust/Form/Flow/Source) are excluded from Advanced Storage Linker statistics.\n\nHardness: 3.0, blast resistance: 10.0.

adm.manual.item.advNetworkLinkBlock=Aggregates and displays full AE2 network statistics.\n\nAuto-refresh: every 20 ticks it scans all ME Drives and ME Chests in the connected network.\n\nCollects 8 metrics: Items used/total bytes, Items used/total types, Fluids used/total bytes, Fluids used/total types.\n\nRight-click forces immediate refresh and shows stats in chat.\n\nCan be bound to a Data Monitor for continuous in-world display of any of the 8 metrics (selectable via NBT path).\n\nHardness: 3.0, blast resistance: 10.0.

adm.manual.item.data_imprint=Imprints block data into the tool for Data Monitors to read and display.\n\nFeatures:\n- Imprint: Sneak+right-click any TileEntity to save coordinates, block type, and full NBT snapshot.\n- Bind: Sneak+right-click a Data Monitor to add the imprinted block as a data source.\n- View: Plain right-click opens a JSON tree viewer for finding correct NBT paths.\n- Clear: Sneak+right-click air to reset the tool.\n\nUnlike Data Loom cells (Dust/Form/Flow): the Imprint Tool only observes and records — it does not weave new items or fluids from the AE network.\n\nStack size: 1. Creative tab: Tools.

adm.manual.item.advance_storage_link_cell=An upgrade component for the Advanced Storage Linker. Implements ICellWorkbenchItem for AE2 Cell Workbench compatibility.\n\nUpgrade slots: 2 (supports Fuzzy and Inverter cards).\n\nConfigurable filters: set which items to display in the Advanced Storage Linker via the cell's partition slots.\n\nOre dictionary filter support: filter by ore dictionary names.\n\nFluid and Essentia markers: mark specific fluids or Thaumcraft essentia types to display.\n\nFuzzy modes: supports AE2's various fuzzy comparison levels.\n\nWorks with standard AE2 storage bus slot configuration.

adm.manual.item.advance_planner=A persistent, reusable task manager stored as an item with NBT data.\n\nRight-click: opens the planner GUI where you can add, edit, complete, delete, reorder, and merge entries.\n\nSneak+right-click: toggles the HUD overlay that shows your tasks on screen.\n\nFeatures: auto-numbered entries, creation timestamps, completion status tracking, stats display (Total/Done/Pending), entry reordering (move up / move to top), multiple planner items supported in one inventory, full NBT persistence across logouts.\n\nMerging: combine multiple planners into one. Two modes: By Time (sorts by creation date) or By Index (preserves order, renumbers).\n\nHUD: fully customizable position, scale, width, max display count, and custom title.\n\nStack size: 1. Creative tab: Tools.

adm.manual.item.data_dust_loom_cell=Basic data loom cell. Weaves AE network data into dust items.\n\nRestriction: GT dust prefix items only; cannot mark AdvanceDataMonitor items.\n\nDefault rate: 1 item/s ([dataDustLoomCell] configurable). Tooltip caches effective rate when markers or amplifier cards change.\n\nPlace in ME Drive/Chest, mark dusts in Cell Workbench. Weave Amplifier cards only (default 4×/card, [dataLoomCell] configurable).\n\nAdvanced Storage Linker: internal stored items are excluded from Advanced Storage Linker statistics.

adm.manual.item.data_form_loom_cell=Advanced data loom cell. Full data weaving — any item except this mod.\n\nRestriction: any item except AdvanceDataMonitor items.\n\nDefault rate: 1 item/s ([dataFormLoomCell] configurable).\n\nPlace in ME Drive/Chest, mark items in Cell Workbench. Weave Amplifier cards only.\n\nAdvanced Storage Linker: internal stored items are excluded from Advanced Storage Linker statistics.

adm.manual.item.data_flow_cell=Fluid data loom cell. Weaves network data into fluids.\n\nRestriction: any fluid marker; AdvanceDataMonitor items cannot be used as markers.\n\nDefault rate: 1000 mB/s = 1 bucket/s ([dataFlowCell] separate config).\n\nPlace in fluid channel of ME Drive/Chest. Weave Amplifier cards only.\n\nAdvanced Storage Linker: internal stored fluids are excluded from Advanced Storage Linker statistics.

adm.manual.item.data_tide_loom_cell=Advanced fluid loom cell (upgrade of Data Flow Cell). Weaves tides of network data into fluids — up to 63 types (enchanted glint).\n\nRestriction: same as Data Flow Cell.\n\nDefault rate: 1000 mB/s ([dataFlowCell] config).\n\nPlace in fluid channel of ME Drive/Chest. Weave Amplifier cards only.\n\nAdvanced Storage Linker: internal stored fluids are excluded from Advanced Storage Linker statistics.

adm.manual.item.data_source_loom_cell=Essentia data loom cell. Weaves network data into Thaumcraft essentia (stored as aspect fluids in GTNH).\n\nRestriction: essentia fluids / aspect types only.\n\nDefault rate: 1000 mB/s ([dataSourceLoomCell] configurable). Settles every 5 seconds.\n\nPlace in fluid channel of ME Drive/Chest. Weave Amplifier cards only.\n\nAdvanced Storage Linker: internal stored essentia is excluded from Advanced Storage Linker statistics.

adm.manual.item.weave_amplifier=Dedicated amplifier for Data Loom cells. Default 4× output per card (configurable in [dataLoomCell] weaveAmplifierRateMultiplier), max 8 cards — multiplies with other cards.\n\nWorks on Dust/Form/Flow/Source cells.\n\nAE acceleration cards are NOT accepted.

adm.manual.item.super_weave_amplifier=Super Weave Amplifier Card. Default 16× per card (configurable in [dataLoomCell] superWeaveAmplifierRateMultiplier), stacks multiplicatively with normal cards.\n\nWarning: many cards can flood the AE network instantly!

adm.manual.item.superOrange=A legendary item with immense power. When carried in your inventory or held, it grants abilities governed by config/AdvanceDataMonitor.cfg [superOrange] and per-item NBT toggles:\n\nControls:\n- Right-click: toggle drone and projectile immunity (item NBT toggle)\n- Sneak + right-click: toggle matter ball and drop multiplier (item NBT toggle)\n- Anvil rename: set head nameplate text\n\n1. Mine Any Block: instantly break any block when held (including GT ores).\n\n2. Head Effects: custom nameplate + rotating halo (OrangeBuff.png). Hidden for yourself in first person; visible in third person and to others. Disable globally with headEffectsEnabled.\n\n3. Matter Ball and Drop Multiplier: when enabled, mined drops auto-convert to Avaritia matter clusters (merge existing or create new), multiplied by dropMultiplier (default x2). Disable globally with dropMultiplierEnabled, or per-item with sneak+right-click.\n\n4. Companion Drone: the body picks a new random point within 3 blocks of you every second (height offset droneFollowHeight), stays near you, and intercepts projectiles (spawns temporary intercept drones per incoming projectile). When hostiles are nearby, combat clones split off to fight; the body never joins combat. Clones deal true armor-bypassing damage. Scan range/damage/rate/max clones are configurable. Right-click toggles drone and projectile immunity.\n\n5. Projectile Immunity: follows the drone toggle (requires projectileImmunityEnabled in config).\n\nAcquisition: 0.1% dungeon/mineshaft chests, 0.05% mob kills.\n\nStack size: 1. Creative tab: Tools.

adm.manual.data_monitor.system_overview_title=System Overview
adm.manual.data_monitor.system_overview_text=The Data Monitor system visualizes TileEntity NBT data as in-world rendered graphics. The pipeline:\n\nData Source (e.g. AE2 linker block) -> Data Imprint Tool imprints NBT snapshot -> binds to Data Monitor -> Monitor reads NBT value every N ticks -> renders chart/text in world.\n\nFour block types work together: Advance Data Monitor (display), Crafting Linker (CPU data), Advanced Storage Linker (inventory data), Network Linker (aggregate stats).\n\nEach monitor face (6 sides) has independent bindings - you can show different data on each face, or the same data on all faces.\n\nRendering uses GL11 + Tessellator with 128-block view range.

adm.manual.data_monitor.setup_title=Network Setup
adm.manual.data_monitor.setup_text=Step-by-step network setup:\n\n1. Place an Advance Data Monitor where you want the display. It auto-records its position and orientation on placement.\n\n2. Place linker blocks adjacent to AE2 cables in your network. Crafting Linker near CPUs, Advanced Storage Linker near drives, Network Linker anywhere on the network.\n\n3. Linkers auto-detect nearby AE2 networks through cable adjacency. They must receive AE2 power.\n\n4. Linkers have internal tick timers (20 ticks = 1 second) for auto-refresh.\n\n5. Craft a Data Imprint Tool. Sneak+right-click the linker block to imprint its data.\n\n6. Sneak+right-click the Advance Data Monitor to add the imprinted source.\n\n7. Right-click the Advance Data Monitor to open configuration GUI. Configure each binding's display settings.\n\nAll blocks: hardness 2.0-3.0, blast resistance 5.0-10.0, iron block texture, custom TESR rendering.

adm.manual.data_monitor.binding_title=Data Imprint Binding Flow
adm.manual.data_monitor.binding_text=Complete Data Imprint binding flow:\n\n1. Sneak+right-click a target TileEntity with the Data Imprint Tool. It records: XYZ coordinates, block registry name, metadata, full NBT dump. For GregTech machines, also captures mName (machine display name).\n\n2. Sneak+right-click a Data Monitor. If the tool has an imprinted coordinate, it is added to the monitor's data bound list for the current face (auto-deduplication, max 100).\n\n3. Open Data Monitor GUI. Each binding appears as a configurable entry with default settings (cyan color, 0.3 scale, 20 tick interval, 100 data limit).\n\n4. For direct NBT tracking: edit the dataName field in the GUI to set the NBT path (e.g. "Items" for item count).\n\n5. For AE2 linker blocks: the monitor auto-detects the link type (Crafting/Storage/Network) and uses the appropriate data processing method.\n\nThe Imprint Tool only records data; weaving matter from the AE network requires Data Loom cells (Dust/Form/Flow).

adm.manual.data_monitor.data_types_title=Chart & Data Types
adm.manual.data_monitor.data_types_text=Supported chart types for numerical data:\n\nLine Chart - plots values over time with a continuous line. Best for monitoring trend changes (e.g. power levels, item counts).\nBar Chart - discrete bars for each data point. Good for comparing snapshots.\n3D Bar Chart - same as bar but with depth rendering for visual depth.\nWaterfall - shows cumulative increases/decreases. Useful for resource flow tracking.\nDifference - shows delta (change) between consecutive readings.\n\nAE2 text display types:\nStorage mode - renders item icons with names and counts in a grid (configurable columns, spacing, icon size).\nCrafting mode - renders template-expressions as formatted text with live variable substitution.\nNetwork mode - renders numeric values (bytes, types) as text or bars.\n\nAll chart types support: color customization, axis configuration, grid lines, title display, scaling, opacity control.

adm.manual.data_monitor.main_gui_title=Main Configuration GUI
adm.manual.data_monitor.main_gui_text=Right-click a Data Monitor to open its 470x270 configuration GUI. From here you manage all data bindings:\n\nLeft panel - Body/Screen visibility toggles, facing direction picker, Add binding button, Show/Hide individual bindings.\n\nRight panel - Per-binding configuration:\n  Data tab: dataType picker (line/bar/3dbar/waterfall/difference for chart, or crafting/storage for AE2 text).\n  Chart tab: line color, line width, grid settings, axis colors, title text/color/scale, X/Y range, update interval, data limit.\n  Position tab: X/Y/Z offsets and rotation angles for in-world placement on the monitor face.\n  AE2 tab (when applicable): template expressions for crafting, display toggles for storage, scope mode.\n\nBottom - Save/Cancel buttons. All settings persist in block NBT.

adm.manual.data_monitor.chart_config_title=Advanced Configuration
adm.manual.data_monitor.chart_config_text=Every chart binding supports these detailed settings (stored per-binding in NBT):\n\nVisual: lineColor (hex RGB, default 00FFFF), lineWidth (default 3.0), gridLineWidth, axisLineWidth, axisLineColor, axisFontColor, displayNameColor, gridLineAlpha, nameAlpha, axisFontAlpha, dataLineAlpha.\n\nTypography: displayName (title text), displayNameScale, axisFontScale, tickLengthFactor.\n\nData: name (NBT path), dataLimit (max points, 2-9999), yMin, yMax, interval (ticks >= 20), xRange, yRange.\n\nPosition: xOffset, yOffset, zOffset, rotationX, rotationY, rotationZ - all support decimal values and negative numbers.\n\nAE2 craft: craftingTemplate (template expression), monitorNetworkWide (true=all CPUs, false=single), textAlign (0=left/1=center/2=right), textScale, textAlpha.\n\nAE2 storage: storageColumns, storageSpacing, storageIconScale, storageLinespacing, storageColor, showItemCount/Delta/Name toggles, sort modes, items/fluids/essentia filters, storageCellIndex.\n\nAll numeric values accept decimal precision for pixel-perfect tuning.

adm.manual.ai_assistant.overview_title=AI Assistant Overview
adm.manual.ai_assistant.overview_text=The AI Assistant leverages OpenAI-compatible LLM APIs to control your AE2 systems with natural language. Press O (default) to open the 600x450 chat window.\n\nCore capabilities:\n- Crafting: order single or batch AE2 crafting jobs. Supports up to 8 tasks per prompt. Multi-step confirmation with candidate selection.\n- Withdrawal: extract items/fluids from AE2 storage into your inventory. Batch withdraw support. Partial withdrawal when inventory is full.\n- Queries: check storage overview (items+fluids with icons), wireless power/steam levels, AE2 recipes/patterns, detailed item counts, byte usage with infinite cell detection.\n- World info: current weather, time (ticks + day count), player position/coordinates/facing, biome name/temperature/rainfall, inventory space.\n- Teleport: scan Draconic Evolution Advanced Dislocator (TeleporterMKII) in inventory, display saved destinations, execute cross-dimension teleport with fuzzy name matching.\n- Planner: add/list/complete/delete/modify planner entries via text commands.\n- Cancel: abort pending operations and cancel queued AE2 crafting jobs at any time.

adm.manual.ai_assistant.setup_title=API Configuration
adm.manual.ai_assistant.setup_text=The AI Assistant uses OpenAI-compatible APIs. Default provider is DeepSeek (free tier available).\n\nSettings window (gear icon in chat) or /admai command:\n\nAPI Key: your provider key. Can also set DEEPSEEK_API_KEY environment variable. Supports DeepSeek, OpenAI, OpenRouter, Anthropic Claude, Google Gemini, Alibaba Qwen, Zhipu GLM, Moonshot Kimi, ByteDance Doubao, SiliconFlow, Mistral, Groq, MiniMax, Volcengine, and more.\n\nBase URL: provider endpoint (default https://api.deepseek.com). Pre-configured URLs for 13+ providers via /admai provider <name>.\n\nModel: model name (default deepseek-chat). Supports tab-completion for common models.\n\nAdvanced: timeout (5-300s), maxTokens (1-8192), temperature (0.0-2.0), streaming mode, web search toggle, debug logging.\n\nPrivacy: first use requires privacy confirmation (data sent to provider). One-time per player.\n\nConfiguration stored in config/AdvanceDataMonitor.cfg and persists across sessions.

adm.manual.ai_assistant.usage_title=Chat Interface & Workflow
adm.manual.ai_assistant.usage_text=Chat window layout (600x450): message history (top, scrollable), input field (bottom), action buttons (Send, Clear, Close, Settings, Menu, Search toggle, Cancel).\n\nBasic workflow:\n1. Type a request, e.g. "Order 64 iron ingots". Press Enter or Send.\n2. If intent is clear, the assistant searches AE2 network for matching items and shows numbered candidates.\n3. Type the number to confirm (e.g. "1"). The order is submitted.\n4. For batch orders: "Order 64 iron and 32 gold". Confirm line by line, then "confirm" to submit all.\n5. For queries: "Show my storage" returns item/fluid list with icons. "How much power?" shows EU/t and capacity.\n6. Menu button lists all 22+ features with numbers. Type a number to invoke directly.\n\nMulti-task: AI can return up to 8 tasks per prompt. Order tasks execute first, then withdrawal tasks.\n\nCancel any time by typing "cancel". This clears the session and cancels pending AE2 craft jobs.\n\nMarkdown rendering: chat responses support headers (# ## ###), bold (**), code blocks (```), lists, and inline code.

adm.manual.ai_assistant.intents_title=Intent Types Reference
adm.manual.ai_assistant.intents_text=The assistant recognizes 24 intent types. Here's what each does:\n\nAE2 COMMANDS:\nORDER_ITEM - submit a single craft order. Returns numbered candidates from AE2 pattern list.\nORDER_BATCH - submit multiple craft orders at once. Line-by-line confirmation, then batch submission.\nWITHDRAW_ITEM - extract items from AE2 storage to inventory. Shows current stock as candidates.\nWITHDRAW_BATCH - batch withdraw multiple items. Supports partial withdraw when inventory full.\nQUERY_RECIPE - search AE2 patterns by name. Returns recipe details (inputs, outputs).\nQUERY_STORAGE - full storage overview: items (by count), fluids, with icons and K/M/T formatting.\nQUERY_JOBS - list pending AE2 crafting jobs.\nQUERY_ITEM_COUNT - detailed item/fluid counts from storage network.\nQUERY_BYTES - byte usage breakdown with infinite cell detection (AE2Things).\nCANCEL - abort session and cancel queued AE2 craft jobs.\n\nENERGY QUERIES:\nQUERY_POWER - wireless energy network power level and capacity.\nQUERY_STEAM - wireless steam network steam amount and status.\n\nWORLD QUERIES:\nQUERY_WEATHER - dimension, rain/thunder state, sky visibility.\nQUERY_TIME - world time (ticks), day count, day/night status, time until dawn/dusk.\nQUERY_POSITION - player XYZ, chunk coords, facing direction (N/S/E/W).\nQUERY_BIOME - biome name, temperature, rainfall, humidity.\nQUERY_INVENTORY - free/used/total inventory slots.\n\nTELEPORT (requires DE Advanced Dislocator):\nTELEPORT - scan dislocator, show destinations, teleport by name/number.\nTELEPORT_LIST - list all saved destinations on dislocator.\n\nPLANNER:\nPLAN_ADD/CREATE/LIST/COMPLETE/DELETE/MODIFY - full planner CRUD operations via AI.\n\nSYSTEM:\nCLARIFY - prompts user for clarification when intent is ambiguous.\nCHAT - normal conversation, no action triggered.

adm.manual.ai_assistant.commands_title=In-Game Commands
adm.manual.ai_assistant.commands_text=/admassistant - AI Assistant management:\n  /admassistant help - show help\n  /admassistant lexicon - show lexicon config file path\n  /admassistant reloadLexicon - reload lexicon (OP required)\n\n/admai - AI configuration management:\n  /admai key <api_key> - set API key\n  /admai clearKey - remove saved key\n  /admai model <name> - set model (tab-completes common models)\n  /admai base <url> - set API base URL (tab-completes known providers)\n  /admai provider <name> - preset for deepseek/openai/openrouter/anthropic/gemini/qwen/glm/kimi/doubao/siliconflow/mistral/groq/minimax/volcengine\n  /admai network on|off|toggle - enable/disable network requests\n  /admai search on|off|toggle|auto|openai|openrouter|dashscope|zhipu|generic-tools - web search control\n  /admai status - show current config\n\nBoth commands: no OP required (except reloadLexicon). Available to all players.

adm.manual.ai_assistant.examples_title=Conversation Examples
adm.manual.ai_assistant.examples_text=Try these prompts to get started:\n\nSingle crafting: "Order 256 copper wire"\nBatch crafting: "Order 64 iron plates, 32 gold plates, and 128 redstone"\nWithdraw items: "Withdraw 64 iron ingots"\nStorage query: "Show me my storage overview"\nFluid query: "How much pyrotheum do I have?"\nPower check: "How much power do I have?"\nSteam check: "What's my steam level?"\nRecipe lookup: "What recipes do I have for HV circuits?"\nByte check: "How many bytes are free in my AE2 network?"\nWeather: "What's the weather like?"\nTime: "What time is it?" or "How long until dawn?"\nPosition: "Where am I?"\nBiome: "What biome is this?"\nInventory: "How much inventory space do I have?"\nTeleport: "Teleport me to my base" or "List my teleport points"\nPlanner: "Add a plan: build fusion reactor" then "List my plans" then "Complete plan 1"\n\nChain commands: "Order 64 iron, withdraw 32 gold, and show my storage"\n\nUse the Menu button if you're unsure what to ask. Type "cancel" anytime to abort.

adm.manual.planner_teleport.overview_title=Planner & Teleport Overview
adm.manual.planner_teleport.overview_text=The Advance Planner is your personal task management tool with full NBT persistence. The Teleport feature integrates with Draconic Evolution's Advanced Dislocator for quick travel.\n\nBoth systems are tightly integrated with the AI Assistant - you can manage plans and teleport destinations entirely through chat commands.\n\nThis chapter covers using the planner GUI, HUD customization, planner merging, and teleport setup.

adm.manual.planner_teleport.planner_usage_title=Planner GUI & Basic Usage
adm.manual.planner_teleport.planner_usage_text=Right-click the Advance Planner item to open its GUI. The interface shows your entries as a scrollable list with action buttons.\n\nCreating entries:\n- Click the + button or an empty slot to add a new entry.\n- Type your task text and press Enter to save.\n- Entries auto-number (1, 2, 3...) and record creation timestamp.\n\nManaging entries:\n- Click an entry to edit its text.\n- Toggle the checkbox to mark complete/incomplete.\n- Trash icon deletes the entry (re-numbers remaining entries).\n- Up arrow moves entry up one position.\n- Top arrow moves entry to position 1.\n\nPlanner stats: header shows Total / Completed / Pending counts.\n\nSneak+right-click toggles the HUD overlay. Chat message confirms HUD on/off status.\n\nKeyboard shortcut: press P to open the planner from your hotbar.\n\nMultiple planners: you can have several planner items, each with independent entries. The merge function combines them.

adm.manual.planner_teleport.planner_entries_title=Entry Management Details
adm.manual.planner_teleport.planner_entries_text=Each planner entry stores four fields in NBT:\n- slotIndex: auto-incrementing number (1, 2, 3...). Auto-renumbers on deletion.\n- text: the task description text you entered.\n- timestamp: creation time (System.currentTimeMillis(), displayed as yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm).\n- completed: boolean flag, toggleable via checkbox.\n\nPersistence: all entries are stored in the item's NBT under the "plannerEntries" tag list. Data survives:\n- Logout/login\n- Item transfer (moving between inventories)\n- Item duplication\n- Breaking and picking up\n\nHUD rendering: uses HudRenderUtil for positioning, scaling, and text wrapping. Supports up to 50 displayed lines with scroll wheel navigation in the GUI.\n\nStats display: "Total N | Done N | Pending N" at the top of the planner GUI.

adm.manual.planner_teleport.planner_merge_title=Planner Merging
adm.manual.planner_teleport.planner_merge_text=When you have multiple planner items (e.g. from other players, creative mode, or accidental duplication), merge them into one:\n\n1. Open any planner GUI.\n2. Click the Merge button. The mod scans your inventory for all planner items.\n3. A merge confirmation window appears showing: "Found N planners with M total entries to merge".\n4. Choose merge mode:\n   By Time - sorts all entries by their creation timestamp, newest first.\n   By Index - preserves the original slot order from each planner, appending planners sequentially (first planner's entries 1..N, then second planner's entries...).\n5. Click Confirm Merge. A new merged ItemStack is created. The original planners remain in inventory (you can discard them).\n\nThe merged planner gets a new nextSlotIndex, renumbering all entries sequentially.\n\nThis function uses mergePlanners() / mergeMultiplePlanners() static methods on ItemAdvancePlanner.

adm.manual.planner_teleport.planner_hud_title=HUD Configuration
adm.manual.planner_teleport.planner_hud_text=The HUD overlay displays your planner entries on screen while playing. Full customization:\n\nHUD Config (accessible from planner GUI):\n- Max Display: number of entries shown (1-20, default 5).\n- Pos X/Y: normalized screen position (0.0=left/top, 1.0=right/bottom, default 1.0/0.0 = top-right).\n- Scale: size multiplier (0.5-3.0, default 1.0).\n- Width: text area width in pixels (80-600, default 160).\n- Custom Title: optional header text (empty = no title).\n\nPreview window: shows your HUD position and size in real-time. Scroll wheel adjusts scale, Shift+scroll adjusts width.\n\nAll HUD settings are stored per-planner in the item's NBT (hudEnabled, hudMaxDisplay, hudPosX/Y, hudScale, hudWidth, hudTitle). Different planner items can have completely different HUD configs.\n\nRange limits are enforced by Config.java: plannerHudMin/Max values for each setting.\n\nHUD rendering uses HudRenderUtil for background, text wrapping, positioning, and scaling calculations.

adm.manual.planner_teleport.teleport_title=Teleport System
adm.manual.planner_teleport.teleport_text=The AI Assistant integrates with Draconic Evolution's Advanced Dislocator (com.brandon3055.draconicevolution.common.items.tools.TeleporterMKII) for teleportation.\n\nRequirements:\n- An Advanced Dislocator (TeleporterMKII) in your inventory.\n- At least one saved destination on the gem (added via DE's own interface).\n\nHow it works:\n1. The assistant scans your inventory for TeleporterMKII items.\n2. Reads the "Locations" NBT tag list from each gem.\n3. Each location has: X, Y, Z, Dimension, Name.\n4. Displays destinations as a numbered list with dimension info.\n5. Confirm by number or fuzzy name match.\n\nExecution:\n- Same dimension: setPositionAndUpdate() for instant teleport.\n- Cross-dimension: uses configurationManager.transferPlayerToDimension() with a custom Teleporter instance.\n\nDimensions are resolved by stored DimentionName (DE uses this typo internally), standard names (Nether/Overworld/The End), or custom dimension IDs.\n\nName matching: exact match preferred, falls back to substring matching if no exact match found.\n\nExample AI prompts: "Teleport me to my base", "List my teleport points", "Take me to the mining dimension".

adm.manual.config_reference.intro_title=Configuration Reference
adm.manual.config_reference.intro_text=This chapter documents all configuration options in the mod's .cfg file (config/AdvanceDataMonitor.cfg). The file is auto-generated on first run with default values.\n\nOrganization: 30 options across 4 categories:\n  ai.* (13 options) - API endpoint, key, model, network, search, streaming, debug, privacy, timeout, tokens, temperature.\n  voice.* (7 options) - Voice assistant enable, privacy, STT mode (embedded-vosk/http), base URL, API key, model, timeout.\n  assistant.* (4 options) - Max order amount, max withdraw amount, craft job timeout, max concurrent craft jobs.\n  plannerHudLimits.* (10 options) - Min/Max bounds for HUD display count, position X/Y, scale, and width.\n\nConfiguration can also be changed in-game via:\n- AI Settings GUI (gear icon in AI Chat)\n- /admai command\n- /admassistant reloadLexicon command\n\nScroll this page with your mouse wheel to browse long config entries.

